author: Jordany Martinez
title: Hit Netflix Shows 'Bridgerton', 'One Piece', 'The Gentlemen' And 'Outer Banks' Amongst Series Not Returning Until 2026
text:
According to
Deadline, earlier today Netflix announced its lineup for its 2025 series which included the final seasons of popular shows Squid Game and Stranger Things and the returns of Wednesday, Ginny & Georgia, Monster, Emily In Paris and The Witcher. Although this is a great lineup of returning shows there are many anticipated popular series that will not be coming back until 2026.
Below is Netflix’s announcement titled “YOU’RE NOT READY | NEXT ON NETFLIX 2025.”
Popular shows that were not announced to be returning this year include the fifth and final season of Outer Banks, Season 4 of
Bridgerton and The Lincoln Lawyer, Season 2 of One Piece, The Gentlemen, Avatar: The Last Airbender, Beef, Black Doves and 3 Body Problem as well as Season 7 of Virgin River. Although the listing isn’t set in stone and some series may move up and air later this year instead of the following.
As per
Deadline, in the past, there have been scheduling changes with what Netflix announces would be originally airing during a certain year. For example, the third season of The Lincoln Lawyer and season six of Virgin River were originally not on Netflix’s 2024 list of shows premiering that year but were able to deliver new seasons for the October and December release. The Night Agent‘s second season was originally scheduled to air in 2024 and then was moved to early 2025.
According to
Deadline, fans of some of the series should not be shocked at the wait time for their favorite shows. Jess Brownell showrunner of Bridgerton announced that a two-year gap was expected between seasons of the series following the trend between the second and third seasons. Virgin River and Black Doves recently aired their current seasons on the streaming platform back in December so their not coming back in 2025 for a new installment is understandable. Many of the other series have either just begun production or just wrapped production on their next season.
All series and more are Available to stream on Netflix.
